<br>
I've banned hmm one person from KB boards. there's still a thread about it on the forums. And i've banned him for hacking our guild forums and cutpasting stuff on KB forums that was coming from our guild forums.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I don't buy your arguments for God loot. Points distribute loot far more fairly, if you're using God loot, it's just a way of whoring power. It's undemocratic by its very nature. Why should a group of a few members of your guild have the right to determine who gets loot for the rest of the guild? Maybe if people felt they had some influence and that their opinions mattered, they'd play more and your turnover wouldn't be so insanely high. People aren't happy getting officer scraps.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
That's the usual old discussion between dkp and awarding. However the reality is that both systems work. Oh and as far as lootwhoring goes, take a moment and look at my magelo, then compare to the other rogues.<br>
<br>
If you take a look at some topguild dkp systems, some of the more complicated ones, you will realize that their intent is not to share loot evenly, but rather to MAKE SURE that the oldtime clique of players that stayed active till the start has NO competition whatsoever for the stuff they might want.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I actually did God loot for a while when I was running Promethian Order, I know what it's all about and how it works, and I moved the guild to DKP, reducing my own power dramatically, but giving every member a say in his own destiny. Our turnout went through the roof after we switched. (Note: I'm not now in Promethian Order, nor have I been for some time. I don't actively play everquest anymore.)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Like i said, different guilds will work better with one or another system. our turnout became steadily higher some months ago when we GOT RID of dkp<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>If God loot guilds really wanted to be democratic, but had a genuine belief that God loot was superior, then why not rotate the council of people who award loot through all members of the guild? That would give everyone a say at least.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Little difference, i don't run a council for loot. i decide all awards personally, without asking officers opinions except in rare cases<br>
