<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>First of all, it's the best choice for guild advancement.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I disagree completely.  The turnover you have because people are upset they have no say in their own destiny more than outweighs the advantages of being able to gear up a MT or other needed personnel.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>rewarding members not only for presence<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
In theory this could be true, but the fact is that it's more about mood than anything else.  There are so many variables to consider that no human being, no matter how hard he tries, can come close to being fair in taking all these variables into account.  I know, I tried, and I realized it was impossible.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>allowing xfer regearing<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
A good DKP system allows this too.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>avoiding loot whoring<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Loot whoring is infinitely more of a problem in God loot guilds than in DKP guilds.  In DKP you can only buy what you have points for (assuming the system doesn't suck).  At least all people would be on the same footing and there wouldn't be a few elite who have the right to do whatever they want.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>avoiding hate between members based on loot<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This is also a much, much greater problem in God loot guilds.  People in DKP guilds just recognize that people get loot because they earned it and got points.  There is tremendous tension in every single God loot guild I have ever heard of.  Lots of people like to deny it, but behind the scenes there are constant murmurs and questioning of every single call.<br>
<br>
