<br>
This is actually very true with some systems.  Afterlife is an example of such a system.  I don't know if it was designed with this intent in mind, I think rather that it was not, but it does have this effect.  This happens in any DKP system without good inflation adjustment.  Essentially, some members accumulate so many points that they can buy everything they want for the next 10 years and never run out of DKP.  I know the system in PO doesn't have this AT ALL.  There is no benefit in the system for being an older member.  In flawed DKP systems it's a problem, in good ones, it's not.  Personally, I'd rather be in a DKP system either way.  At least in a bad DKP system, I'd know that several years down the line, I'd stand a chance of getting good stuff.  It's better than being in a God loot system where you know that no matter how much you play, and no matter how long you are there, you may never have a chance at being treated fairly.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Little difference, i don't run a council for loot. i decide all awards personally, without asking officers opinions except in rare cases<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You don't think it's a bit egocentric that you and you alone know better than the rest of the guild?  That's just so arrogant I can hardly comprehend it.  I was suggesting a council of people that would rotate, and which you would not be a permanent member of.  i.e. Every member would have an equal role in deciding loot.<br>
<br>
Oh, and you mentioned your rogue, but do you have any other characters that can get loot on raids over other players?  I've even heard rumors that officers in TCR played multiple characters as mains in the guild without telling the guild they were 2 boxing.<br>
